The paper deals with range searching in higher dimensions, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also introduces a data structure for halfspace range counting, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves partitioning a set of points, which is a common technique in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The construction of a spanning tree with small crossing number is related to graph theory (cs.GR), and the paper also discusses the use of hyperplanes, which is a topic in scientific computing (cs.SC).
